Package org.ejbca.core.model.ra.userdatasource

Class BaseUserDataSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cesecore.internal.UpgradeableDataHashMap
      • org.ejbca.core.model.ra.userdatasource.BaseUserDataSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, IUpgradeableData
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CustomUserDataSourceContainer
    public abstract class BaseUserDataSource
extends UpgradeableDataHashMap
implements Serializable, Cloneable
    BaseUserDataSource is a basic class that should be inherited by all types of userdatasources in the system. Contains data like description, applicable CAs and modifyable fields.
    Version:
    $Id: BaseUserDataSource.java 22675 2016-01-29 16:07:49Z samuellb $

      • removeUserData

        public abstract boolean removeUserData​(AuthenticationToken admin,
                                       String searchstring,
                                       boolean removeMultipleMatch)
                                throws MultipleMatchException,
                                       UserDataSourceException
        Optional method used to remove user data from a user data source. It's up to the implementation if it should be supported or not. Removes user data that matches the given search string.
        Parameters:
        admin - Admin
        searchstring - the string the user data source that should be removed
        removeMultipleMatch - use to indicate if all entries should be removed it the search string
        Returns:
        true if the user was remove successfully from at least one of the user data sources. matches more than one, if false will a UserDataSourceException be thrown if more than one User data matches the search string.
        Throws:
        MultipleMatchException - On fail
        UserDataSourceException - if a communication or other error occurs.
